"n.准确，精确 【英】 n.准确,精确(precisi on; accuracy) 【考】 nicety : precision / illusion : fantasy(精确和精确/ 幻想和幻想) n. 精确; 谨慎(要求细心和精确对待的性质) 【记】源于: nice(adj 美好的; 挑剔的; 精密的) 【类】nicety: precision = illusion: fantasy精确 = 幻想(同义) 【记】nice 美好，精确 nicety (n.)  mid-14c., ""folly, stupidity,"" from Old French niceté ""foolishness, childishness, simplicity,"" from nice ""silly"" (see nice). Underwent sense evolution parallel to nice, arriving at ""minute, subtle point"" 1580s and ""exactitude"" in 1650s. Phrase to a nicety ""exactly"" is attested from 1795."
